
[1]watchful

   WATCHFUL, a. Vigilant; attentive; careful to observe; observant;
   cautious. It has of before the thing to be regulated, as to be watchful
   of ones behavior; and against, before the thing to be avoided, as to be
   watchful against the growth of vicious habits.
